  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "The term \"SSC\" typically refers to the Staff Selection Commission in India, which is responsible for recruiting staff for various posts in the ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India. The types of postings under SSC can include a variety of positions across different government departments. Some common positions include:\n\n1. **SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level)**: This exam leads to various posts such as:\n   - Assistant Audit Officer\n   - Assistant Section Officer\n   - Inspector of Income Tax\n   - Tax Assistant\n   - Junior Statistical Officer\n   - Central Excise Inspector\n   - Customs Inspector\n\n2. **SSC CHSL (Combined Higher Secondary Level)**: This exam is for higher secondary level candidates and can lead to posts such as:\n   - Lower Division Clerk (LDC)\n   - Data Entry Operator (DEO)\n   - Postal Assistant/Sorting Assistant\n\n3. **SSC JE (Junior Engineer)**: This recruitment is for engineering graduates for the following roles:\n   - Junior Engineer (Civil, Mechanical, Electrical)\n\n4. **SSC MTS (Multi Tasking Staff)**: This is for candidates who have passed the 10th standard and can lead to various group C posts in different ministries and departments.\n\n5. **SSC CPO (Central Police Organisation)**: This exam is for recruitment into the police forces of Central Government, including:\n   - Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police\n   - CAPF (Central Armed Police Forces)\n\n6. **SSC Stenographer**: This recruitment is for stenographer posts in various ministries.\n\n7. **SSC GD (General Duty)**: This is for recruiting constables in the General Duty category in various Central Armed Police Forces.\n\n8. **SSC Scientific Assistant**: For recruitment in the India Meteorological Department.\n\nThese positions can vary based on the specific recruitment notifications released by the SSC, and new roles can be introduced as per government needs. Each position has specific eligibility criteria, exam patterns, and selection processes. Always check the official SSC website for the most accurate and updated information regarding postings and recruitment processes.",
